line_1: And like the rose, her emblem, dies.
line_2: With the dreams of youth she flies,

line_1: And Freedom dies,
line_2: And hear her cries:

line_1: Shoots back the bolt, and all his courage dies:
line_2: The warder at the door his key applies,

line_1: And his heart within him dies;
line_2: From their sight the caitiff flies,

line_1: All sense of pity in my bosom dies,
line_2: And direful tumults of reproaches rise:

line_1: Till every worldly thought within me dies,
line_2: And earth's gay pageants vanish from my eyes;

line_1: " My brother bleeds and dies! "
line_2: " That low my Hengist lies!
